1
00:01:16,355 --> 00:01:18,585
Yeah! Go, buddy, go!

2
00:01:19,524 --> 00:01:22,015
That baby's going scared!

3
00:01:49,688 --> 00:01:51,019
Give me one.

4
00:01:51,189 --> 00:01:52,349
Get them.

5
00:01:52,524 --> 00:01:53,582
Hey, boys!

6
00:01:54,092 --> 00:01:55,855
How y'all doing?

7
00:01:56,194 --> 00:01:59,595
What are you looking at?
You want to get shot?!

8
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:03,089
Go, baby!

9
00:02:04,936 --> 00:02:06,597
-You got it!
-Pearl Harbor!

10
00:02:19,384 --> 00:02:21,045
Here's another one!

11
00:02:21,219 --> 00:02:22,208
Watch this!

12
00:02:22,788 --> 00:02:23,948
100 points!

13
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:37,564
It's a beautiful day, isn't it?

14
00:03:03,428 --> 00:03:04,827
Bye, Tonya.

15
00:03:16,174 --> 00:03:17,937
Clean up that mess, boy.

16
00:03:20,779 --> 00:03:21,609
Hungry?

17
00:03:24,449 --> 00:03:25,780
You're having nothing?

18
00:03:25,951 --> 00:03:27,680
I'm having them.

19
00:03:29,788 --> 00:03:31,619
Shit.

20
00:03:31,857 --> 00:03:33,290
Bye, girls.

21
00:03:33,792 --> 00:03:35,020
Let's go!

22
00:03:38,130 --> 00:03:39,119
You're on the house.

23
00:03:39,297 --> 00:03:40,628
Harry Rex!

24
00:03:40,799 --> 00:03:42,699
All those weekends...

25
00:03:42,868 --> 00:03:43,857
...fishing...

26
00:03:44,035 --> 00:03:46,697
...lounging, opportunities lost...

27
00:03:46,872 --> 00:03:48,703
...to renovate yourself.

28
00:03:48,874 --> 00:03:50,865
Tragic, just tragic, Jake.

29
00:03:53,879 --> 00:03:55,312
Makes Carla happy.

30
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:58,643
Spent 4 marriages trying to figure
out what makes women happy.

31
00:03:58,817 --> 00:04:02,548
You spent 4 marriages trying to
figure out what makes you happy.

32
00:04:04,489 --> 00:04:05,478
Maybe that's it.

33
00:04:05,657 --> 00:04:06,988
Yeah, maybe.

34
00:04:07,159 --> 00:04:07,887
Swiggy?

35
00:04:08,059 --> 00:04:10,050
Lord, let my car be fixed today.

36
00:04:10,228 --> 00:04:11,320
Oh, dear.

37
00:04:27,412 --> 00:04:28,401
Who's that?

38
00:04:31,349 --> 00:04:32,077
She's young.

39
00:04:33,518 --> 00:04:34,246
Hold this.

40
00:04:34,419 --> 00:04:35,681
What're you doing?

41
00:04:35,854 --> 00:04:39,085
If they're old enough to crawl,
they're in the right position.

42
00:04:39,257 --> 00:04:40,519
What're you doing?

43
00:04:40,692 --> 00:04:42,250
What're you going to do?

44
00:04:49,034 --> 00:04:50,695
50 points!

45
00:04:50,869 --> 00:04:52,200
You good, boy!

46
00:04:53,438 --> 00:04:54,268
Shut up!

47
00:04:55,407 --> 00:04:56,738
Daddy!

48
00:04:58,610 --> 00:04:59,770
Go, bud.

49
00:05:00,278 --> 00:05:01,040
Shut up!

50
00:05:02,447 --> 00:05:03,539
Shut up!

51
00:05:05,050 --> 00:05:05,778
I'll kill you.

52
00:05:05,951 --> 00:05:06,576
My turn.

53
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:09,950
There you are.

54
00:05:10,121 --> 00:05:11,213
Shut up!

55
00:05:11,723 --> 00:05:12,553
Daddy!

56
00:05:23,935 --> 00:05:25,266
Mama!

57
00:05:37,148 --> 00:05:37,910
What is this?

58
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:39,482
Groceries!

59
00:05:39,651 --> 00:05:41,141
Y'all see her?

60
00:06:23,695 --> 00:06:26,186
How many appointments
do we have today?

61
00:06:26,364 --> 00:06:28,195
Not a one.

62
00:06:28,366 --> 00:06:31,358
But it is the first of the
month again and guess what.

63
00:06:31,536 --> 00:06:35,700
The checks are pouring in.
We have enough money to pay our debts.

64
00:06:35,874 --> 00:06:37,705
That'll be your last drink.

65
00:06:38,610 --> 00:06:41,477
Just keep us no more than one
month behind on any vendor.

66
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,142
You have been drinking.

67
00:06:43,882 --> 00:06:44,974
2 months.

68
00:06:45,150 --> 00:06:48,051
These are the most delinquent.
The rent's in there.

69
00:06:49,554 --> 00:06:52,045
I appreciate the practice, Captain.

70
00:06:52,223 --> 00:06:54,555
But you could've left me a few clients.

71
00:07:02,233 --> 00:07:04,724
Baby, here's Daddy coming.

72
00:07:13,578 --> 00:07:15,910
I'm here, baby. Daddy's here.

73
00:07:17,082 --> 00:07:17,912
Daddy...

74
00:07:18,083 --> 00:07:21,018
...l'm sorry I dropped the groceries.

75
00:07:21,186 --> 00:07:24,849
That's all right, baby.
That's all right, baby.

76
00:07:25,090 --> 00:07:26,682
That's all right.

77
00:07:52,917 --> 00:07:54,248
Look at this.

78
00:08:22,247 --> 00:08:23,305
Billy Ray.

79
00:08:24,082 --> 00:08:28,075
Sorry, sir, but we don't allow
no African-Americans here.

80
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:29,909
Billy Ray Cobb...

81
00:08:30,088 --> 00:08:31,988
...you and Willard must come with me.

82
00:08:32,824 --> 00:08:34,416
I ain't moving.

83
00:08:34,592 --> 00:08:36,753
The girl you took for a ride...

84
00:08:37,662 --> 00:08:38,424
What girl?

85
00:08:38,596 --> 00:08:40,996
I got bad news for you. She didn't die.

86
00:08:41,433 --> 00:08:45,665
So unless there's another redneck
asshole with a yellow truck...

87
00:08:45,837 --> 00:08:48,101
...with a Confederate flag--

88
00:08:48,273 --> 00:08:49,262
Blue gums...

89
00:08:49,441 --> 00:08:51,671
...get out of here and grab a branch.

90
00:08:51,843 --> 00:08:55,609
Unless you got an explanation for
why this was in your truck...

91
00:08:56,848 --> 00:08:57,678
...you're going to jail.

92
00:08:57,849 --> 00:08:58,838
Get up.

93
00:09:00,285 --> 00:09:02,014
You go to hell, nigger.

94
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:03,452
Goddamn!

95
00:09:05,190 --> 00:09:06,623
Come here.

96
00:09:09,194 --> 00:09:12,095
Now, you earn the
right to remain silent!

97
00:09:12,464 --> 00:09:14,364
Here, just like you like them.

98
00:09:15,533 --> 00:09:18,297
-Sugar, today I'm going to have--
-Go to hell.

99
00:09:18,470 --> 00:09:20,631
I'll just watch baby eat his.

100
00:09:20,805 --> 00:09:23,035
I didn't handle her husband's divorce.

101
00:09:23,208 --> 00:09:25,142
I'm shriveling away here.

102
00:09:25,310 --> 00:09:26,368
I'm shriveling.

103
00:09:28,146 --> 00:09:29,545
What's up?

104
00:09:30,215 --> 00:09:33,150
Didn't you defend Billy
Ray Cobb a few years back?

105
00:09:34,385 --> 00:09:35,374
What for?

106
00:09:36,654 --> 00:09:38,053
Caught him selling dope.

107
00:09:38,223 --> 00:09:40,487
Spent time in Parchman.
Got out last year.

108
00:09:41,059 --> 00:09:43,721
I think some Memphis
lawyer handled that.

109
00:09:43,895 --> 00:09:45,157
Why do you ask?

110
00:09:45,663 --> 00:09:48,325
Picked him up for rape.
Him and Willard.

111
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:49,660
Who'd they rape?

112
00:09:51,069 --> 00:09:52,832
You know Carl Lee Hailey?

113
00:09:53,004 --> 00:09:55,063
I defended his brother Lester.

114
00:09:57,342 --> 00:09:59,173
It was his little girl.

115
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:03,342
Little Tonya?

116
00:10:08,853 --> 00:10:09,911
How old's she?

117
00:10:11,422 --> 00:10:12,855
She's ten.

118
00:10:55,633 --> 00:10:56,964
Mr. Willard...

119
00:10:57,135 --> 00:10:58,625
...l'm Sheriff Walls.

120
00:10:59,137 --> 00:11:01,571
My mama voted for you.

121
00:11:03,408 --> 00:11:05,569
I seen you play for the Rams.

122
00:11:07,745 --> 00:11:11,579
Way I figure, a nigger
sheriff's okay, been on TV.

123
00:11:14,419 --> 00:11:15,818
No offense.

124
00:11:19,157 --> 00:11:20,647
What's your full name?

125
00:11:21,092 --> 00:11:22,923
James Lewis Willard.

126
00:11:26,864 --> 00:11:29,128
4, which is a difference of 110.60.

127
00:11:33,871 --> 00:11:35,304
Who's there?

128
00:11:54,592 --> 00:11:55,889
Carl Lee.

129
00:12:01,899 --> 00:12:03,161
How is she?

130
00:12:04,602 --> 00:12:06,502
She's holding on.

131
00:12:07,739 --> 00:12:10,606
Doctor says she ain't out
of the woods yet, though.

132
00:12:18,116 --> 00:12:20,744
They worked her over something good.

133
00:12:28,192 --> 00:12:32,754
You remember them 4 white boys
raped that black girl last year?

134
00:12:38,436 --> 00:12:40,028
They got off, didn't they?

135
00:12:50,882 --> 00:12:53,715
I was in a jam, you'd help
me out, wouldn't you?

136
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:57,779
Sure, Carl Lee.

137
00:12:59,891 --> 00:13:01,882
What kind of jam you talking of?

138
00:13:02,894 --> 00:13:05,055
You got a daughter, Jake.

139
00:13:05,296 --> 00:13:06,888
What would you do?

140
00:13:17,809 --> 00:13:19,902
You dream some good dreams.

141
00:13:20,078 --> 00:13:21,909
Good night, Daddy.

142
00:13:22,914 --> 00:13:24,245
Night, baby.

143
00:13:40,498 --> 00:13:42,489
Is she asleep?

144
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:43,928
She's so sweet.

145
00:13:44,102 --> 00:13:45,763
Yeah, she is...

146
00:13:45,937 --> 00:13:47,336
...next to you.

147
00:13:48,106 --> 00:13:51,507
When I look at her though, I
cannot help but think about...

148
00:13:51,709 --> 00:13:52,767
...Tonya.

149
00:13:54,345 --> 00:13:55,277
Don't.

150
00:13:58,783 --> 00:14:00,842
Don't do that to yourself.

151
00:14:07,024 --> 00:14:08,116
Something wrong?

152
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:11,225
Tonya's father...

153
00:14:11,529 --> 00:14:13,292
...Carl Lee Hailey...

154
00:14:13,798 --> 00:14:15,288
...came to the office today.

155
00:14:17,468 --> 00:14:19,868
Man's heart is torn wide open, baby.

156
00:14:20,238 --> 00:14:21,796
I don't know, but...

157
00:14:21,973 --> 00:14:24,464
...seemed like he was
going to do something.

158
00:14:24,876 --> 00:14:26,241
Like what?

159
00:14:27,745 --> 00:14:29,975
Something like killing those boys.

160
00:14:30,648 --> 00:14:31,979
Was he serious?

161
00:14:35,820 --> 00:14:37,879
I don't know. I don't know.

162
00:14:38,055 --> 00:14:40,046
It could be just hurt talking.

163
00:14:41,392 --> 00:14:44,657
But when you think it's
possible those two animals could...

164
00:14:45,163 --> 00:14:46,755
...go free...

165
00:14:47,899 --> 00:14:49,833
...and be walking the streets....

166
00:14:55,339 --> 00:14:56,670
I don't know.

167
00:14:58,509 --> 00:15:02,502
After what that man has been through,
he's capable of anything.

168
00:15:03,681 --> 00:15:05,774
Somebody should do something.

169
00:15:06,584 --> 00:15:08,518
You should call Sheriff Walls.

170
00:16:06,744 --> 00:16:09,577
...to release the
owner from assessment.

171
00:16:13,484 --> 00:16:15,349
I hope I'm having a heart attack...

172
00:16:15,486 --> 00:16:17,647
...'cause then I get to sue you!

173
00:16:18,089 --> 00:16:20,922
Don't stand on ceremony, come on in.

174
00:16:21,092 --> 00:16:22,992
What? No clients?

175
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:26,152
Just waiting to pick yours up on appeal.

176
00:16:26,364 --> 00:16:28,924
And you, are you on vacation?

177
00:16:29,934 --> 00:16:32,266
Fortunately for me, my lovely...

178
00:16:32,603 --> 00:16:34,764
...divorce doesn't go on vacation.

179
00:16:35,006 --> 00:16:36,598
However...

180
00:16:36,774 --> 00:16:40,369
...not even the richest, most
ridiculous settlement I get...

181
00:16:40,511 --> 00:16:44,106
...will be as satisfying as
watching those two hyenas...

182
00:16:44,448 --> 00:16:46,507
...get what's coming to them.

183
00:16:51,289 --> 00:16:52,620
Oh, dear.

184
00:16:55,293 --> 00:16:58,285
I'm a fool for those
German-type convertibles.

185
00:17:01,132 --> 00:17:03,396
Come on, let's get to court.

186
00:17:03,534 --> 00:17:06,401
Lucien thinks the two
hyenas just might get off.

187
00:17:06,537 --> 00:17:07,902
You saw Lucien?

188
00:17:08,205 --> 00:17:09,797
When? Where?

189
00:17:09,974 --> 00:17:11,134
How is he?

190
00:17:11,309 --> 00:17:13,209
Has he been eating better?

191
00:17:15,913 --> 00:17:17,471
Just curious.

192
00:17:19,617 --> 00:17:24,418
Refresh my recollection, how long
were you and Lucien together?

193
00:17:24,555 --> 00:17:27,991
We were never together.
I was his secretary for 20 years.

194
00:17:28,159 --> 00:17:30,059
Come on, old girl.

195
00:17:30,227 --> 00:17:31,216
You can tell us.

196
00:17:31,429 --> 00:17:32,726
He was your boyfriend.

197
00:17:32,930 --> 00:17:36,730
I am an upstanding, God-fearing,
respectable woman...

198
00:17:36,934 --> 00:17:40,995
...with unimpeachable morals who
has been happily married 27 years.

199
00:17:41,172 --> 00:17:45,074
And I have never had or ever
will have any boyfriend!

200
00:17:45,443 --> 00:17:46,740
And if I did...

201
00:17:46,944 --> 00:17:51,506
...it would not be that old
pickled scoundrel Lucien Wilbanks!

202
00:17:56,253 --> 00:17:58,517
-She did him, a lot.
-Definitely.

203
00:18:05,663 --> 00:18:06,891
Step back.

204
00:18:08,666 --> 00:18:10,463
Come on out.

205
00:18:13,804 --> 00:18:15,965
Boys, today's your big day.

206
00:18:16,173 --> 00:18:19,904
We'll go to the courthouse,
the judge will set your bail...

207
00:18:20,077 --> 00:18:22,739
...then we'll come back,
nice and peaceful.

208
00:18:22,913 --> 00:18:26,974
If I get any trouble out of you,
I'm going to integrate this jail.

209
00:19:54,071 --> 00:19:56,403
Mama, Daddy's home!

210
00:19:58,075 --> 00:20:01,408
Hannah, let's go inside for a minute.

211
00:20:03,681 --> 00:20:06,081
Let's find a book.

212
00:20:39,817 --> 00:20:43,218
Jake, are you hurt?
Jake, what happened to you?!

213
00:20:43,554 --> 00:20:46,216
Honey, are you okay?
What happened to you?

214
00:20:46,390 --> 00:20:49,826
What is this? What is
going on with you?!

215
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:52,326
Jake, baby, are you okay?

216
00:20:52,630 --> 00:20:54,393
What happened?

217
00:21:46,283 --> 00:21:47,443
I'll see you.

218
00:22:01,398 --> 00:22:02,797
Will the sheriff comment?

219
00:22:02,967 --> 00:22:04,958
He might make a statement, or not.

220
00:22:05,135 --> 00:22:06,966
-Is it first-degree murder?
-I don't know.

221
00:22:09,406 --> 00:22:10,964
Here comes the sheriff.

222
00:22:11,141 --> 00:22:13,302
I got no comment. No comment.

223
00:22:13,477 --> 00:22:16,412
Hey, Jake. Carl Lee
said you'd be coming.

224
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:18,648
Are you an attorney?

225
00:22:18,816 --> 00:22:22,718
I'll make a statement.
Get these vans out of here.

226
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:25,218
Give us something for our newscasts.

227
00:22:44,942 --> 00:22:46,842
Didn't think I'd do it, did you?

228
00:22:50,581 --> 00:22:52,173
How you holding up?

229
00:22:56,587 --> 00:23:00,182
I ain't had nothing against them
till they messed with my baby.

230
00:23:00,858 --> 00:23:04,692
And I feel sorry for their
mamas and their daddys, but...

231
00:23:05,863 --> 00:23:08,024
...l ain't sorry for what I done.

232
00:23:11,101 --> 00:23:12,363
How's Looney?

233
00:23:14,972 --> 00:23:17,031
You blew his knee off his leg.

234
00:23:17,875 --> 00:23:19,706
Doctors are still with him.

235
00:23:24,114 --> 00:23:25,706
What'll happen to me?

236
00:23:27,051 --> 00:23:31,385
There's going to be a preliminary
hearing. Probably tomorrow.

237
00:23:32,222 --> 00:23:34,554
Then Buckley'll push for a fast trial.

238
00:23:35,492 --> 00:23:36,720
Who's Buckley?

239
00:23:36,894 --> 00:23:38,225
Rufus Buckley...

240
00:23:38,495 --> 00:23:39,553
...district attorney.

241
00:23:39,730 --> 00:23:43,723
He's mean, he's ambitious and he'll
eat this up because of the publicity.

242
00:23:43,901 --> 00:23:45,732
But you've beat him?

243
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:47,230
Yeah.

244
00:23:48,072 --> 00:23:49,903
Not in a murder case.

245
00:23:53,577 --> 00:23:55,238
Think I can win?

246
00:23:56,013 --> 00:23:58,504
All depends on the jury, Carl Lee.

247
00:23:59,516 --> 00:24:01,507
Pick the right jury, and you'll walk.

248
00:24:02,820 --> 00:24:04,913
DA picks the jury and...

249
00:24:05,089 --> 00:24:06,420
...you get the gas.

250
00:24:11,595 --> 00:24:13,756
How much a case like this cost?

251
00:24:16,667 --> 00:24:18,157
Probably 50 grand.

252
00:24:20,771 --> 00:24:22,762
I can pay maybe ten.

253
00:24:30,047 --> 00:24:31,105
There're not a...

254
00:24:31,849 --> 00:24:35,285
...lot of white lawyers would've
took my brother's case.

255
00:24:35,686 --> 00:24:38,052
You did and got him off.

256
00:24:38,856 --> 00:24:41,051
I figure there's people out there...

257
00:24:41,191 --> 00:24:44,558
...tired of all the
raping and killing and...

258
00:24:44,695 --> 00:24:48,859
...they'd be sympathetic to a man who
took the law into his own hands...

259
00:24:49,066 --> 00:24:50,693
...even if he is black.

260
00:24:57,808 --> 00:25:01,300
You said you'd help me
out if I was in a jam.

261
00:25:02,079 --> 00:25:04,309
Well, I'm in one now.

262
00:25:05,983 --> 00:25:07,314
What do you say?

263
00:25:09,820 --> 00:25:11,811
What can you tell us, sheriff?

264
00:25:11,989 --> 00:25:12,819
Comment?

265
00:25:12,990 --> 00:25:14,582
Are you with the police?

266
00:25:14,725 --> 00:25:15,817
I'm a lawyer.

267
00:25:15,993 --> 00:25:17,722
Are you Hailey's attorney?

268
00:25:18,595 --> 00:25:20,722
Are you Mr. Hailey's attorney?

269
00:25:21,331 --> 00:25:22,491
Yes, I am.

270
00:25:22,666 --> 00:25:23,496
Your name?

271
00:25:23,667 --> 00:25:26,363
Brigance. Jake Brigance.
That's with one 'G.'

272
00:25:34,044 --> 00:25:35,534
Hailey's hired an attorney.

273
00:25:36,213 --> 00:25:37,305
