And when I graduate...

526
00:39:28,945 --> 00:39:32,676
...l intend to spend a glorious career
stomping out the death penalty.

527
00:39:33,182 --> 00:39:34,672
Let's see, what else?

528
00:39:34,851 --> 00:39:36,443
Genius runs in my family.

529
00:39:36,686 --> 00:39:38,278
You'll get me on the way up...

530
00:39:38,421 --> 00:39:41,754
...and I really think now
is a good time to grab me.

531
00:39:43,359 --> 00:39:44,951
Anything else I should know?

532
00:39:45,261 --> 00:39:47,456
Let's see, anything else?

533
00:39:47,597 --> 00:39:49,963
My father's rich so I'll work for free.

534
00:39:52,035 --> 00:39:53,468
What do you think?

535
00:39:56,606 --> 00:39:59,473
I think I'll drop this brief
off in Noose's night slot.

536
00:40:00,043 --> 00:40:01,772
Go home, see my family.

537
00:40:01,978 --> 00:40:04,105
Thanks, but I can handle the case.

538
00:40:09,552 --> 00:40:11,884
You might look at these precedents.

539
00:40:12,055 --> 00:40:13,613
State vs. Cooper...

540
00:40:13,790 --> 00:40:16,623
...and State vs. Roundtree.
Revenge killers, both acquitted.

541
00:40:20,296 --> 00:40:21,729
You'll change your mind.

542
00:40:24,133 --> 00:40:25,122
See you.

543
00:40:32,008 --> 00:40:32,997
Get out.

544
00:40:33,142 --> 00:40:34,006
Come on.

545
00:40:36,746 --> 00:40:38,907
Come here. Come on.

546
00:41:01,604 --> 00:41:02,935
Mr. Cobb...

547
00:41:03,106 --> 00:41:06,769
...this is Stump Sisson,
Grand Dragon of Mississippi.

548
00:41:08,277 --> 00:41:09,835
You were looking for us?

549
00:41:11,614 --> 00:41:14,447
You were right to call us,
Mr. Cobb.

550
00:41:15,451 --> 00:41:17,681
They say the Klan is dead.

551
00:41:19,355 --> 00:41:22,119
Klan don't show up
for a few years and...

552
00:41:22,291 --> 00:41:24,452
...people say the Klan is dead.

553
00:41:24,794 --> 00:41:27,194
Fact is, it just looks dead.

554
00:41:27,697 --> 00:41:30,461
The Klan has always been right there...

555
00:41:31,067 --> 00:41:32,864
...under the surface...

556
00:41:34,137 --> 00:41:38,471
...just waiting for the opportunity
to deliver God's justice.

557
00:41:39,642 --> 00:41:40,973
I want help.

558
00:41:41,144 --> 00:41:43,135
I want to kill that nigger.

559
00:41:43,312 --> 00:41:44,301
Niggers got...

560
00:41:44,480 --> 00:41:46,641
...plenty of protection nowadays.

561
00:41:47,817 --> 00:41:49,808
They got the NAACP...

562
00:41:49,986 --> 00:41:51,715
...and the A.C.L.U.

563
00:41:52,488 --> 00:41:54,888
Even the federal government.

564
00:41:55,091 --> 00:41:56,149
Hell...

565
00:41:56,726 --> 00:41:58,387
...white folks ain't got a chance.

566
00:42:00,730 --> 00:42:02,595
Except the Klan.

567
00:42:06,669 --> 00:42:08,398
I'm going to tell you what.

568
00:42:10,173 --> 00:42:13,404
You get 5 or 6 of your
friends of similar thinking...

569
00:42:13,843 --> 00:42:15,242
...and we'll initiate...

570
00:42:15,411 --> 00:42:17,743
...the Madison County Klavern.

571
00:42:19,615 --> 00:42:21,606
Even make you leader.

572
00:42:23,653 --> 00:42:25,348
Now, you tell me...

573
00:42:26,122 --> 00:42:27,749
...who's that nigger's lawyer?

574
00:42:28,691 --> 00:42:30,124
Local boy.

575
00:42:30,259 --> 00:42:33,524
His name's Brigance.
He's got a pretty good reputation.

576
00:42:35,431 --> 00:42:36,921
He got family?

577
00:42:37,133 --> 00:42:40,125
Yes, sir. He has a wife and a daughter.

578
00:42:43,639 --> 00:42:44,936
Good.

579
00:43:26,582 --> 00:43:27,913
Why's he here?

580
00:43:28,084 --> 00:43:29,813
Calm down, son.

581
00:43:29,986 --> 00:43:31,920
Calm down. Come on, now.

582
00:43:32,688 --> 00:43:34,918
He has no right after what he did.

583
00:43:36,425 --> 00:43:38,825
Don't get your mom upset now.

584
00:43:52,775 --> 00:43:53,605
Looney?

585
00:43:55,511 --> 00:43:56,603
Dwayne?

586
00:44:01,284 --> 00:44:03,275
I made Ozzie bring me.

587
00:44:08,724 --> 00:44:10,624
Shit, Dwayne, we...

588
00:44:10,960 --> 00:44:13,019
We knowed each other since childhood.

589
00:44:18,301 --> 00:44:19,734
It's my fault.

590
00:44:20,803 --> 00:44:22,634
No matter what's said in court...

591
00:44:23,806 --> 00:44:28,243
...l knew what I was doing, and I sure
didn't intend to hurt you, but...

592
00:44:28,377 --> 00:44:29,969
...just them two boys.

593
00:44:35,318 --> 00:44:37,980
I know it don't mean much now, but...

594
00:44:39,555 --> 00:44:40,817
...l'm sorry.

595
00:44:48,764 --> 00:44:52,495
Some folks think a black man can't
receive a fair trial in the South.

596
00:44:52,902 --> 00:44:56,668
I'll show the men and women of the South
will look past color and see the truth.

597
00:44:56,839 --> 00:44:58,773
It sure is a nigger's world.

598
00:44:58,908 --> 00:45:00,398
Not for long.

599
00:45:02,511 --> 00:45:03,671
Boys...

600
00:45:04,080 --> 00:45:06,844
...l'm very proud to invite
you to become soldiers...

601
00:45:07,016 --> 00:45:10,179
...in the war to protect our
Christian homes and families.

602
00:45:10,353 --> 00:45:12,014
To resurrect our country...

603
00:45:12,188 --> 00:45:14,782
...from the fires of racial degradation.

604
00:45:15,191 --> 00:45:16,590
And to make whites...

605
00:45:16,792 --> 00:45:20,353
...the sole masters of
our nation's destiny.

606
00:45:21,364 --> 00:45:23,298
What I'm saying, fellas...

607
00:45:24,367 --> 00:45:26,426
...it's time for the nigger to pay.

608
00:45:29,305 --> 00:45:31,034
Is your telephone broken?

609
00:45:31,207 --> 00:45:33,539
We just had the number changed.

610
00:45:33,709 --> 00:45:35,438
That's what the operator said.

611
00:45:35,611 --> 00:45:37,306
To an unlisted number.

612
00:45:37,813 --> 00:45:39,804
Sorry you had to come up here.

613
00:45:39,949 --> 00:45:42,042
I should've called you, but this case--

614
00:45:42,218 --> 00:45:45,710
This case has us all
worried sick about you all.

615
00:45:45,955 --> 00:45:47,718
This thing could get ugly.

616
00:45:47,890 --> 00:45:49,448
And dangerous.

617
00:45:49,892 --> 00:45:52,122
Jake, he shot them in cold blood.

618
00:45:53,329 --> 00:45:55,627
They raped, almost killed his daughter.

619
00:45:57,466 --> 00:45:59,127
What if that happened to Hannah?

620
00:46:03,239 --> 00:46:04,729
May we ask a few questions?

621
00:46:04,907 --> 00:46:06,397
Can we get a quote?

622
00:46:06,642 --> 00:46:09,406
Excuse me, I'm going to
go take a few questions.

623
00:46:09,645 --> 00:46:11,135
This isn't the time.

624
00:46:11,347 --> 00:46:13,645
It's really good for Carl Lee.

625
00:46:15,985 --> 00:46:17,850
Thank you for coming.

626
00:46:22,591 --> 00:46:25,355
Guess we'll have to read
about it in the papers.

627
00:47:22,918 --> 00:47:24,215
Praise Jesus!

628
00:47:39,668 --> 00:47:40,430
Reverend?

629
00:47:42,571 --> 00:47:44,232
I'm lsaiah Street.

630
00:47:44,440 --> 00:47:46,931
It's an honor to meet you, Reverend.

631
00:47:47,076 --> 00:47:49,169
I saw you march with Dr. King.

632
00:47:51,180 --> 00:47:53,444
The struggle continues today...

633
00:47:54,083 --> 00:47:55,345
...here in Canton.

634
00:47:55,951 --> 00:47:59,682
Carl Lee Hailey's on trial because
he's black. No other reason.

635
00:48:00,956 --> 00:48:03,447
These people are with the NAACP.

636
00:48:05,694 --> 00:48:06,683
How do you do?

637
00:48:06,862 --> 00:48:07,954
How are you?

638
00:48:10,099 --> 00:48:14,536
The black community's concerned
that Mr. Hailey's attorney...

639
00:48:14,703 --> 00:48:17,695
...isn't sensitive to the
needs of the movement.

640
00:48:18,607 --> 00:48:19,596
The NAACP...

641
00:48:20,876 --> 00:48:24,039
...wishes to provide
him with a new lawyer.

642
00:48:26,048 --> 00:48:30,212
We need to raise funds to
support Carl Lee Hailey.

643
00:48:31,554 --> 00:48:34,614
I don't know, Reverend.
Time's awfully tight here.

644
00:48:36,492 --> 00:48:38,119
Obviously...

645
00:48:38,294 --> 00:48:40,888
...we would expect you to take...

646
00:48:41,063 --> 00:48:44,624
...a modest administration
fee for your troubles.

647
00:49:11,093 --> 00:49:12,924
Your loyalty...

648
00:49:13,128 --> 00:49:15,096
...has been forged...

649
00:49:15,264 --> 00:49:17,027
...in a baptism of fire.

650
00:49:18,701 --> 00:49:20,362
Rise, knights...

651
00:49:20,536 --> 00:49:22,367
...of the Ku Klux Klan...

652
00:49:23,706 --> 00:49:25,697
...and let your brethren...

653
00:49:25,941 --> 00:49:27,704
...never regret...

654
00:49:29,512 --> 00:49:32,276
...they believed you worthy...

655
00:49:32,715 --> 00:49:34,444
...of fellowship.

656
00:49:39,889 --> 00:49:41,880
Welcome to the Klan.

657
00:49:54,069 --> 00:49:55,969
I need to talk to Jake.

658
00:49:56,138 --> 00:49:58,402
He's not in. Who's calling?

659
00:50:02,144 --> 00:50:03,133
Mickey Mouse.

660
00:50:03,646 --> 00:50:05,580
-Who?
-Mickey Mouse.

661
00:50:06,248 --> 00:50:08,079
Get out right now.

662
00:50:08,651 --> 00:50:09,640
Who's this?

663
00:50:09,718 --> 00:50:11,413
Get your daughter out of the
house right now!

664
00:50:17,159 --> 00:50:18,922
Hannah, what is it?

665
00:50:19,161 --> 00:50:20,594
Oh, my God!

666
00:50:21,830 --> 00:50:23,263
Max, come on!

667
00:50:23,432 --> 00:50:25,093
Fire!

668
00:50:25,267 --> 00:50:26,757
Fire!

669
00:50:32,775 --> 00:50:36,176
It's a good thing Hastings
was nearby and got here fast.

670
00:50:36,345 --> 00:50:38,336
The whole place could've burned.

671
00:50:39,014 --> 00:50:40,276
I appreciate it.

672
00:50:40,449 --> 00:50:41,780
Take care.

673
00:50:49,959 --> 00:50:51,517
She asleep, baby?

674
00:50:53,362 --> 00:50:56,695
The Ku Klux Klan is burning
crosses on our lawn.

675
00:50:56,865 --> 00:50:59,959
There's been no Klan
around here for years.

676
00:51:00,135 --> 00:51:04,868
This is just some dorks with too much
time on their hands and too many beers.

677
00:51:08,477 --> 00:51:09,466
I'm sorry.

678
00:51:09,645 --> 00:51:10,805
About what?

679
00:51:12,214 --> 00:51:15,650
That you weren't home when they
almost burned our house down?

680
00:51:16,385 --> 00:51:18,717
That you missed supper and didn't call?

681
00:51:18,887 --> 00:51:22,152
That you've become more interested
in getting on the news...

682
00:51:22,324 --> 00:51:24,155
...than in your own family?

683
00:51:24,326 --> 00:51:28,057
That Hannah comes home bawling
because kids call her a nigger-lover?

684
00:51:28,230 --> 00:51:30,892
What exactly are you sorry about, Jake?

685
00:51:39,575 --> 00:51:41,338
Remember the other night?

686
00:51:43,345 --> 00:51:46,007
I told you Carl Lee came by the office?

687
00:51:46,181 --> 00:51:48,081
Remember what we talked about?

688
00:51:48,684 --> 00:51:49,673
Calling Ozzie.

689
00:51:54,023 --> 00:51:56,082
You never called him, did you?

690
00:51:57,593 --> 00:51:59,254
You never called Sheriff Walls?

691
00:52:00,262 --> 00:52:01,854
I didn't call him.

692
00:52:03,198 --> 00:52:06,929
Lord have mercy, Jake,
you had a responsibility.

693
00:52:07,102 --> 00:52:09,195
Carl Lee chose you.

694
00:52:09,371 --> 00:52:12,033
He told you what he was thinking.

695
00:52:12,708 --> 00:52:15,609
He told me what he was thinking,
but I didn't know--

696
00:52:15,778 --> 00:52:19,612
Jake Tyler Brigance, we agreed
you'd call the sheriff.

697
00:52:19,882 --> 00:52:22,214
Now look at everything that's happened.

698
00:52:22,885 --> 00:52:25,547
I am sorry to tell you this, but...

699
00:52:25,721 --> 00:52:29,885
...those 2 boys are dead and you
were in a position to prevent it!

700
00:52:32,728 --> 00:52:34,286
Are you and Daddy fighting?

701
00:52:35,798 --> 00:52:37,060
Come here.

702
00:52:37,232 --> 00:52:38,961
Come here, come here.

703
00:52:40,402 --> 00:52:44,133
Mommy's just upset because some
silly man played a bad joke.

704
00:52:44,306 --> 00:52:45,796
It's nothing.

705
00:52:46,575 --> 00:52:48,736
Nothing at all, okay?

706
00:52:55,317 --> 00:52:57,308
What did the Memphis doctor say?

707
00:52:58,420 --> 00:53:00,251
She's doing good.

708
00:53:01,323 --> 00:53:02,756
Her jaw is healing.

709
00:53:02,925 --> 00:53:04,916
She can't run and jump yet, but...

710
00:53:05,094 --> 00:53:06,652
...it won't be long.

711
00:53:07,830 --> 00:53:09,593
How about the other?

712
00:53:17,506 --> 00:53:19,269
There was too much damage.

713
00:53:21,443 --> 00:53:23,502
She ain't gonna never have kids.

714
00:53:31,687 --> 00:53:34,349
You know, I think about them two boys.

715
00:53:34,523 --> 00:53:36,115
Dead, buried...

716
00:53:36,291 --> 00:53:38,191
...probably starting to rot...

717
00:53:39,128 --> 00:53:42,029
...and I remember them
walking in court...

718
00:53:42,197 --> 00:53:44,188
...one proud, the other scared.

719
00:53:45,701 --> 00:53:47,862
I remember how they fell.

720
00:53:48,036 --> 00:53:52,973
One on top of the other, screaming
and squirming and not going nowhere.

721
00:53:54,977 --> 00:53:57,036
God help me, Gwen, but...

722
00:53:59,214 --> 00:54:01,705
...that's the only
thought gives me comfort.

723
00:54:04,987 --> 00:54:08,150
They took up a collection
for us at church.

724
00:54:08,724 --> 00:54:11,215
Some kind of defense fund.

725
00:54:11,894 --> 00:54:14,556
Reverend Agee gave a good service.

726
00:54:17,733 --> 00:54:20,896
We need some money 'round
the house, Carl Lee...

727
00:54:21,069 --> 00:54:23,731
...for groceries and bills.

728
00:54:24,239 --> 00:54:25,672
How much you got?

729
00:54:27,242 --> 00:54:28,504
Less than 50.

730
00:54:30,345 --> 00:54:32,006
I'll think of something.

731
00:54:35,350 --> 00:54:39,411
How you think you going to get
money when you stuck in jail?

732
00:54:39,588 --> 00:54:41,351
Trust me, Gwen.

733
00:54:46,261 --> 00:54:48,252
I just get scared.

734
00:54:50,098 --> 00:54:51,360
Look here...

735
00:54:52,601 --> 00:54:55,263
...tell me exactly what
Reverend Agee said...

736
00:54:55,437 --> 00:54:58,031
...when he passed around
the collection plate.

737
00:54:58,207 --> 00:55:01,370
I don't care. We're dealing
with life and death here.

738
00:55:01,543 --> 00:55:04,376
-I must talk to my supervisor.
-Go talk to him.

739
00:55:04,546 --> 00:55:05,535
Get out!

740
00:55:05,714 --> 00:55:07,875
How are things at the electric company?

741
00:55:08,050 --> 00:55:11,952
That is the second time this
week I've had to hold him off.

742
00:55:12,621 --> 00:55:13,553
How much we owe?

743
00:55:13,722 --> 00:55:15,053
$2,000.

744
00:55:15,224 --> 00:55:17,624
-How much do we have?
-$100.

745
00:55:17,793 --> 00:55:21,058
Look, this week nothing
has come in at all.

746
00:55:21,230 --> 00:55:24,063
What about Buck Britt's retainer?
There's 2 grand.

747
00:55:24,233 --> 00:55:25,564
That check bounced.

748
00:55:25,734 --> 00:55:27,133
What do you mean?

749
00:55:27,569 --> 00:55:29,298
It bounced, Jake.

750
00:55:29,471 --> 00:55:31,735
It sat on your desk all week.

751
00:55:32,241 --> 00:55:33,970
Not that you'd notice.

752
00:55:35,978 --> 00:55:39,470
Since you took this case, you
stopped talking to your clients...

753
00:55:39,648 --> 00:55:41,479
...you don't take your calls...

754
00:55:41,650 --> 00:55:43,914
...you're obsessed! You are!

755
00:55:43,986 --> 00:55:45,146
You're obsessed!

756
00:55:45,921 --> 00:55:48,651
Your obsession is going to break us!

757
00:55:49,258 --> 00:55:51,920
What's wrong? We've
been through hard times.

758
00:55:52,094 --> 00:55:53,994
No, not like this, Jake.

759
00:55:54,162 --> 00:55:55,823
Not like this.

760
00:55:57,099 --> 00:55:58,999
We've been getting calls.

761
00:55:59,334 --> 00:56:00,494
At home.

762
00:56:00,669 --> 00:56:01,931
Threats.

763
00:56:03,171 --> 00:56:07,608
You know Bud has survived two strokes.
I don't think he'd survive a third.

764
00:56:07,776 --> 00:56:08,936
Why didn't you tell me?

765
00:56:10,279 --> 00:56:11,940
Why, Jake?

766
00:56:12,180 --> 00:56:13,841
Would you drop the case?

767
00:56:19,621 --> 00:56:20,952
Jake Brigance's office.

768
00:56:21,123 --> 00:56:23,023
Until they cut the phones off.

769
00:56:24,359 --> 00:56:25,792
Oh, right.

770
00:56:29,131 --> 00:56:33,033
That was Sheriff Walls.
You better get down to the jail.

771
00:56:40,375 --> 00:56:42,036
What's going on here?

772
00:56:42,711 --> 00:56:43,939
I'm lsaiah Street.

773
00:56:44,112 --> 00:56:45,545
Jake Brigance.

774
00:56:47,382 --> 00:56:49,543
I believe you know Reverend Agee.

775
00:56:49,718 --> 00:56:51,049
And this is...

776
00:56:51,219 --> 00:56:53,949
Norman Reinfeld, I've seen
your picture in the paper.

777
00:56:54,957 --> 00:56:56,788
I assume these boys carry your things.

778
00:56:57,893 --> 00:57:00,623
Just a small part of
my legal defense team.

779
00:57:00,796 --> 00:57:02,127
Pleasure, Mr. Brigance.

780
00:57:03,565 --> 00:57:05,965
If it's a party, where's the beer?

781
00:57:06,401 --> 00:57:07,231
Otherwise...

782
00:57:07,402 --> 00:57:10,394
...your being here seems a bit like
illegal client solicitation...

783
00:57:10,739 --> 00:57:13,071
...with Carl Lee
already having a lawyer.

784
00:57:13,241 --> 00:57:14,469
Just a minute.

785
00:57:14,977 --> 00:57:17,070
Carl Lee invited us here.

786
00:57:19,247 --> 00:57:20,908
Mr. Brigance...

787
00:57:21,817 --> 00:57:23,580
...let me be frank.

788
00:57:23,752 --> 00:57:27,153
Mr. Hailey's case has
far-reaching ramifications.

789
00:57:27,589 --> 00:57:30,149
Carl Lee's acquittal for
killing 2 white men...

790
00:57:30,325 --> 00:57:32,418
...would do more for
black people than...

791
00:57:32,594 --> 00:57:35,995
...any event since we
integrated the schools.

792
00:57:36,164 --> 00:57:39,327
His conviction, on the other
hand, will be a slap at us.

793
00:57:39,501 --> 00:57:41,662
A symbol of deep-seated racism.

794
00:57:41,803 --> 00:57:44,101
Perhaps enough to ignite a nation.

795
00:57:44,272 --> 00:57:46,672
See how important this case is?

796
00:57:46,842 --> 00:57:49,333
Enter Mr. Reinfeld's death squad, right?

797
00:57:49,511 --> 00:57:53,345
It's an unfortunate
nickname, but apropo.

798
00:57:53,515 --> 00:57:57,007
My lawyers and I handle
only capital murder cases.

799
00:57:57,185 --> 00:57:58,447
Of all your cases...

800
00:57:58,620 --> 00:58:02,522
...how many are supposed to be
lost so you can martyr the victim?

801
00:58:03,125 --> 00:58:05,958
How much a defense like that cost?

802
00:58:11,700 --> 00:58:13,361
What, about $100,000?

803
00:58:13,535 --> 00:58:17,631
We are prepared to accept $7,000
in litigation expenses.

804
00:58:18,540 --> 00:58:21,202
Carl Lee doesn't have $7,000.

805
00:58:21,710 --> 00:58:22,699
Do you?

806
00:58:23,211 --> 00:58:24,200
The NAACP...

807
00:58:24,379 --> 00:58:28,873
...has raised $5,000 for Carl
Lee's legal defense fund.

808
00:58:29,051 --> 00:58:32,214
And we raised an additional
$2,000 from local churches.

809
00:58:32,387 --> 00:58:34,048
Let me ask you something.

810
00:58:34,389 --> 00:58:37,381
How much of that cash you
offer my wife and kids?

811
00:58:37,559 --> 00:58:38,890
That money...

812
00:58:39,061 --> 00:58:41,655
...is to go to pay for lawyers' fees.

813
00:58:41,830 --> 00:58:43,991
That ain't what you told the church.

814
00:58:44,666 --> 00:58:47,066
You almost cried when you told them...

815
00:58:47,235 --> 00:58:51,001
...how my family might starve
if they didn't donate.

816
00:58:51,506 --> 00:58:54,498
The money is for you
and your family, but...

817
00:58:54,676 --> 00:58:57,577
...we thought it'd be better
spent on the legal defense.

818
00:58:57,746 --> 00:59:00,078
Speaking of that defense fund...

819
00:59:00,348 --> 00:59:03,181
...can I use that for any lawyer I want?

820
00:59:04,086 --> 00:59:06,179
It's not that simple, Carl Lee.

821
00:59:06,354 --> 00:59:09,084
Actually, it is that simple, Carl Lee.

822
00:59:09,257 --> 00:59:10,747
Unless the NAACP...

823
00:59:10,926 --> 00:59:14,020
...wants to go on record as soliciting
funds under false pretenses.

824
00:59:14,196 --> 00:59:15,356
Listen...

825
00:59:15,530 --> 00:59:17,361
...we raised that money...

826
00:59:17,532 --> 00:59:21,263
...for these men to get you out of
here, not for this cracker to--

827
00:59:21,436 --> 00:59:24,371
Now, hold on. Hold on right there, now.

828
00:59:25,040 --> 00:59:28,100
Let me just get this
straight here, Reverend.

829
00:59:31,213 --> 00:59:33,044
If you don't give my wife...

830
00:59:33,215 --> 00:59:34,773
...that cash...

831
00:59:34,950 --> 00:59:38,716
...l'll see to it everybody in this
town knows you're a lying crook.

832
00:59:39,221 --> 00:59:41,781
Your congregation will
be interested to know...

833
00:59:41,957 --> 00:59:45,290
...Gwen and the kids can't eat
because you want in with the NAACP.

834
00:59:45,460 --> 00:59:47,121
That's right.

835
00:59:47,295 --> 00:59:48,785
When I'm through with you...

836
00:59:48,964 --> 00:59:52,730
...you won't be able to collect
2 cents in the collection plate.

837
00:59:52,901 --> 00:59:56,132
We'll expect the check for
the Hailey family today.

838
00:59:59,074 --> 01:00:01,565
I sure do appreciate your fine work...

839
01:00:01,743 --> 01:00:03,802
...but I'll take my chances with Jake.

840
01:00:05,914 --> 01:00:08,246
Thanks for coming down.

841
01:00:09,084 --> 01:00:11,143
We'll expect that check...

842
01:00:11,319 --> 01:00:14,755
...for Jake's legal services
around the same time today.

843
01:00:18,827 --> 01:00:20,089
Good day, men.

844
01:00:38,680 --> 01:00:40,841
You set that whole thing up.

845
01:00:41,016 --> 01:00:42,847
Couldn't have done it alone.

846
01:00:45,287 --> 01:00:47,278
Make one hell of a team.

847
01:00:47,956 --> 01:00:49,514
You out there.

848
01:00:49,691 --> 01:00:51,022
I'm in here.

849
01:00:51,193 --> 01:00:52,683
We ain't no team.

850
01:01:17,319 --> 01:01:18,980
There's trouble.

851
01:01:20,488 --> 01:01:21,386
Look there.

852
01:01:27,562 --> 01:01:29,393
No, here's trouble.

853
01:01:39,007 --> 01:01:39,905
You are?

854
01:01:40,175 --> 01:01:41,836
Meet Harry Rex Vonner...

855
01:01:42,010 --> 01:01:45,571
...the most effective, morally-
compromised lawyer in the country.

856
01:01:45,747 --> 01:01:47,738
Ellen Roark, brilliant law student.

857
01:01:47,916 --> 01:01:49,008
Do what you will.

858
01:01:49,184 --> 01:01:50,173
Looking forward to it.

859
01:01:52,587 --> 01:01:54,418
This might interest you.

860
01:01:54,589 --> 01:01:59,083
In assessing murder trials, the
insanity plea only makes up 1\/\ overall.

861
01:01:59,261 --> 01:02:04,096
And of the 1\/\ that resulted in acquittal
success rested almost wholly on the--

862
01:02:04,266 --> 01:02:08,862
Defending psychiatrist regardless of the
quality of the psychological testimony.

863
01:02:09,537 --> 01:02:11,437
Shazam. She is brilliant.

864
01:02:11,606 --> 01:02:13,767
"She." That would be me?

865
01:02:13,942 --> 01:02:14,874
Who else?

866
01:02:15,043 --> 01:02:16,101
She would be me.

867
01:02:16,278 --> 01:02:19,042
She is saying that if I
take this plea to trial...

868
01:02:19,214 --> 01:02:22,945
...the verdict will hinge on the
shrink the jury finds more credible.

869
01:02:23,285 --> 01:02:24,877
She will be correct.

870
01:02:25,287 --> 01:02:26,879
She would.

871
01:02:27,555 --> 01:02:29,455
Sure you don't need help?

872
01:02:29,791 --> 01:02:30,621
I do.

873
01:02:30,792 --> 01:02:33,124
I'm hiring. Right now. Me.

874
01:02:33,561 --> 01:02:37,725
Roark, I am sure that I don't need
any help. Thank you, though.

875
01:02:39,968 --> 01:02:43,233
I guess that would just
have to be your loss, then.

876
01:02:44,906 --> 01:02:46,737
Nice to meet you, Morally-Compromised.

877
01:02:47,475 --> 01:02:48,737
Pleasure's all mine...

878
01:02:48,910 --> 01:02:49,968
..."She."

879
01:02:53,815 --> 01:02:57,410
You've got to love the Lord
for making things like that.

880
01:02:57,585 --> 01:03:01,749
Sure you don't want to look at
her rsum? You could use help.

881
01:03:02,657 --> 01:03:06,423
No, I don't want to look at
her rsum, because I have you.

882
01:03:06,928 --> 01:03:07,587
You do?

883
01:03:07,929 --> 01:03:09,089
Yeah, buddy.

884
01:03:09,264 --> 01:03:14,099
This is your chance to put aside your
shady sources and greedy divorcees...

885
01:03:14,269 --> 01:03:16,328
...and do some real law for once.

886
01:03:18,006 --> 01:03:19,837
Mr. Vonner, in short...

887
01:03:20,008 --> 01:03:23,171
...you have the opportunity to
work on a case that matters.

888
01:03:24,446 --> 01:03:25,936
Let me get this straight.

889
01:03:26,114 --> 01:03:30,175
You want me to put aside my
empty, soulless, shady...

890
01:03:30,352 --> 01:03:33,515
...astonishingly lucrative,
divorcee practice...

891
01:03:33,688 --> 01:03:37,784
...come work with you on an unwinnable,
lose-all-my-friends case...

892
01:03:38,860 --> 01:03:40,054
...because it matters?

893
01:03:40,128 --> 01:03:41,857
It's a novel idea, I know.

894
01:03:42,030 --> 01:03:45,022
No way. Never.
Presumptuous little shit.

895
01:03:46,968 --> 01:03:48,128
Goodnight, y'all.

896
01:03:54,142 --> 01:03:55,700
I need the sheriff.

897
01:03:55,877 --> 01:03:57,139
He's asleep.

898
01:03:57,312 --> 01:03:58,870
Well, get him up.

899
01:03:59,047 --> 01:04:00,378
Who is this?

900
01:04:00,548 --> 01:04:02,641
Someone's going to die tonight.

901
01:04:26,408 --> 01:04:27,739
I got him!

902
01:04:28,510 --> 01:04:29,738
Get his ass!

903
01:04:29,911 --> 01:04:31,503
What's in the case?

904
01:04:41,022 --> 01:04:42,080
It's ticking.

905
01:04:42,257 --> 01:04:43,417
What is it?

906
01:04:43,591 --> 01:04:45,183
I ain't saying.

907
01:04:49,864 --> 01:04:50,762
Family out?

908
01:04:53,768 --> 01:04:55,099
It's locked.

909
01:05:00,041 --> 01:05:01,269
Open it.

910
01:05:12,387 --> 01:05:13,445
My God!

911
01:05:13,955 --> 01:05:15,217
Oh, man....

912
01:05:17,559 --> 01:05:18,548
Defuse it.

913
01:05:18,960 --> 01:05:21,224
I'm going to take you and this...

914
01:05:21,296 --> 01:05:23,059
...nigger-lover to hell with--

915
01:05:24,732 --> 01:05:27,462
Ain't nothing more dangerous
than a fool with a cause.

916
01:05:27,635 --> 01:05:31,071
Lay that thing back down there
real easy-like. Let's go.

917
01:05:31,239 --> 01:05:33,139
Carla loves this house.

918
01:05:56,164 --> 01:05:57,256
Come here.

919
01:06:01,102 --> 01:06:03,662
Are you coming to Grandpa's too?

920
01:06:04,005 --> 01:06:06,439
Daddy must stay here and work.

921
01:06:06,774 --> 01:06:09,334
You and your mom have a good time.

922
01:06:09,511 --> 01:06:10,944
You be good.

923
01:06:11,513 --> 01:06:13,003
Go get your stuff.

924
01:06:14,182 --> 01:06:16,616
You said you'd quit if it got dangerous.

925
01:06:16,784 --> 01:06:17,842
I know.

926
01:06:18,019 --> 01:06:20,112
I can't quit now, you know that.

927
01:06:21,022 --> 01:06:24,685
Carl Lee is facing the gas chamber.
The man is counting on me.

928
01:06:25,627 --> 01:06:27,857
I understand that, Jake.

929
01:06:28,196 --> 01:06:30,687
Remember that we're counting on you too.

930
01:06:30,865 --> 01:06:32,628
What if something happens to you?

931
01:06:33,301 --> 01:06:35,462
Nothing's going to happen. Come here.

932
01:06:36,638 --> 01:06:37,366
Hug?

933
01:06:38,873 --> 01:06:41,637
Everything will be okay.
I'll be fine, you'll be fine.

934
01:06:43,545 --> 01:06:44,807
Okay, babe?

935
01:06:46,481 --> 01:06:47,539
I promise.

936
01:06:49,817 --> 01:06:52,047
Don't make promises you can't keep.

937
01:06:56,991 --> 01:06:58,151
You ready?

938
01:07:11,239 --> 01:07:13,730
Good afternoon. Come in.

939
01:07:15,310 --> 01:07:16,504
Good afternoon.

940
01:07:16,644 --> 01:07:19,408
You may come this way.
The judge is upstairs.

941
01:07:19,581 --> 01:07:20,809
Thank you, sir.

942
01:07:29,657 --> 01:07:30,817
Judge Noose.

943
01:07:32,527 --> 01:07:33,926
Thanks for coming.

944
01:07:35,830 --> 01:07:38,321
Heard you had trouble last night.

945
01:07:38,766 --> 01:07:41,929
Makes you wonder about the
sensibleness of taking this case.

946
01:07:42,270 --> 01:07:44,761
This is a beautiful place you have here.

947
01:07:45,340 --> 01:07:47,035
I'll get to the point.

948
01:07:47,175 --> 01:07:51,043
I've thoroughly reviewed
your brief request and...

949
01:07:51,179 --> 01:07:53,044
...a change of venue.

950
01:07:53,681 --> 01:07:58,175
And I agree with you. It's impossible
to find an impartial jury in Canton.

951
01:07:58,353 --> 01:08:03,120
I think it's impossible to find an
impartial jury anywhere in Mississippi.

952
01:08:03,458 --> 01:08:04,857
As such...

953
01:08:05,126 --> 01:08:07,458
...a jury here would be...

954
01:08:07,629 --> 01:08:10,291
...as fair as a jury anywhere else.

955
01:08:10,632 --> 01:08:13,624
So I decided to deny your
request for a change of venue.

956
01:08:16,804 --> 01:08:18,294
I guess that...

957
01:08:18,573 --> 01:08:20,200
...gives me something to appeal.

958
01:08:20,375 --> 01:08:22,070
Actually, no.

959
01:08:23,077 --> 01:08:25,204
I spoke to Judge Dent...

960
01:08:25,647 --> 01:08:29,879
...and he believes that the Supreme
Court would uphold my ruling.

961
01:08:31,085 --> 01:08:33,315
You certainly covered your bases.

962
01:08:36,891 --> 01:08:38,984
You're a good lawyer.

963
01:08:39,494 --> 01:08:41,894
You're bright and ambitious.
Talented.

964
01:08:42,096 --> 01:08:43,222
You could be someone.

965
01:08:43,398 --> 01:08:47,391
You sure you want to be known as
the man that defended that murderer?

966
01:08:47,902 --> 01:08:50,097
Could be very unpopular.

967
01:08:51,172 --> 01:08:52,833
Talk to your client.

968
01:08:53,608 --> 01:08:55,098
He pleads guilty...

969
01:08:55,243 --> 01:08:59,179
...Buckley'll accept manslaughter.
He'll be out in 20.

970
01:08:59,914 --> 01:09:02,906
And how's his wife supposed
to raise his family alone?

971
01:09:03,751 --> 01:09:05,412
Better than being a widow.

972
01:09:07,021 --> 01:09:08,511
Think about it.

973
01:09:09,257 --> 01:09:11,919
Why toss away a promising career?

974
01:09:15,930 --> 01:09:16,862
Good day.

975
01:09:17,198 --> 01:09:18,529
Thanks for coming.

976
01:09:24,205 --> 01:09:26,196
Where the hell is this guy?

977
01:09:26,874 --> 01:09:28,535
Born alcoholic.

978
01:09:28,710 --> 01:09:31,372
But the man cannot hold his liquor.

979
01:09:33,214 --> 01:09:37,275
Allow me to present
Dr. Willard Tyrrel Bass.

980
01:09:37,719 --> 01:09:40,210
Expert witness for the defense.

981
01:09:41,723 --> 01:09:43,657
This is Jake Brigance...

982
01:09:43,791 --> 01:09:45,053
...my protg.

983
01:09:55,570 --> 01:09:57,060
Are you kidding me?

984
01:09:57,238 --> 01:09:58,569
Relax.

985
01:09:58,740 --> 01:10:01,072
When he's sober, he's terrific.

986
01:10:01,976 --> 01:10:03,238
He has his license.

987
01:10:03,678 --> 01:10:05,908
His credentials are impeccable.

988
01:10:10,251 --> 01:10:12,481
Well, I need a drink.

989
01:10:12,754 --> 01:10:14,585
3 in the afternoon?

990
01:10:14,756 --> 01:10:17,486
My, oh, my, what would your wife say?

991
01:10:17,692 --> 01:10:19,990
I am my own man. I drink when I want.

992
01:10:20,194 --> 01:10:22,822
-When did she leave town?
-This morning.

993
01:10:42,917 --> 01:10:43,474
God!

994
01:10:59,133 --> 01:11:00,225
That's enough!

995
01:11:06,307 --> 01:11:08,366
Now you tell your boss...

996
01:11:08,543 --> 01:11:11,034
...next time people are going to die.

997
01:11:45,279 --> 01:11:46,405
Morning.

998
01:11:50,084 --> 01:11:52,075
Nice parking job. Late night?

999
01:12:01,796 --> 01:12:03,423
So, here.

1000
01:12:05,032 --> 01:12:05,930
Thank you.

1001
01:12:06,100 --> 01:12:07,931
Your wife lets you sleep here?

1002
01:12:08,369 --> 01:12:10,098
My wife left town.

1003
01:12:10,538 --> 01:12:11,869
That's too bad.

1004
01:12:12,807 --> 01:12:14,604
Listen, I heard that...

1005
01:12:14,809 --> 01:12:16,800
...Noose turned down your motion.

1006
01:12:20,114 --> 01:12:22,708
It's time I take you to breakfast.

1007
01:12:25,720 --> 01:12:26,880
Lunch.

1008
01:12:28,890 --> 01:12:30,551
Quit playing with that food.

1009
01:12:30,625 --> 01:12:33,958
Y'all come back. You need to
finish that before Christmas.

1010
01:12:34,395 --> 01:12:35,453
Thank you.

1011
01:12:35,630 --> 01:12:36,619
Now....

1012
01:12:36,831 --> 01:12:39,459
You are opposed to the death penalty.

1013
01:12:39,634 --> 01:12:40,965
Why?

1014
01:12:41,135 --> 01:12:41,965
You're not?

1015
01:12:42,970 --> 01:12:44,835
I'm in favor of it.

1016
01:12:44,972 --> 01:12:47,907
I'd like to go back to
hangings if we could.

1017
01:12:48,643 --> 01:12:49,575
You're kidding.

1018
01:12:50,077 --> 01:12:54,741
No. The only problem with the death
penalty is that we do not use it enough.

1019
01:12:57,985 --> 01:13:00,476
Have you told Carl Lee this?

1020
01:13:00,855 --> 01:13:04,848
The men who raped his daughter deserved
the death penalty, not Carl Lee.

1021
01:13:04,992 --> 01:13:07,483
How do you decide who
dies and who doesn't?

1022
01:13:07,662 --> 01:13:12,156
Simple. You take the crime
and you take the criminal.

1023
01:13:12,600 --> 01:13:14,090
Now, say...

1024
01:13:14,268 --> 01:13:16,998
...a crack dealer guns
down an undercover cop.

1025
01:13:17,171 --> 01:13:19,264
You strap him to a chair and turn it on.

1026
01:13:19,440 --> 01:13:22,170
For some reason, I thought
you were a liberal.

1027
01:13:22,677 --> 01:13:24,440
I am a liberal.

1028
01:13:24,612 --> 01:13:28,514
What I am not is a
card-carrying A.C.L.U. radical.

1029
01:13:28,950 --> 01:13:31,441
I don't believe in rehabilitation.

1030
01:13:31,752 --> 01:13:33,185
I believe in safety.

1031
01:13:33,387 --> 01:13:35,014
I believe in justice.

1032
01:13:36,891 --> 01:13:39,689
I see. Well, let me ask you something.

1033
01:13:40,294 --> 01:13:42,125
Ever seen an execution?

1034
01:13:43,531 --> 01:13:44,691
Not that I recall.

1035
01:13:44,899 --> 01:13:47,459
I suggest you go watch
a man be executed.

1036
01:13:47,635 --> 01:13:52,038
You watch him die, watch him beg, watch
him kick and spit the life out of him...

1037
01:13:52,106 --> 01:13:54,404
...until he shits and is gone.

1038
01:13:54,542 --> 01:13:57,477
Then come back and sing
this crap about justice....

1039
01:13:57,812 --> 01:14:01,213
Spare me your Northern
liberal cry-me-a-river...

1040
01:14:01,415 --> 01:14:04,407
...we-are-the-only-enlightened-ones
bullshit.

1041
01:14:04,552 --> 01:14:07,316
I'm sorry, yes, you are the enlightened.

1042
01:14:07,488 --> 01:14:11,424
That's why you brought me to this
diner in this black neighborhood.

1043
01:14:11,559 --> 01:14:15,552
So you can convince me you're
this JFK-meets-Christ white boy.

1044
01:14:15,730 --> 01:14:16,924
Is that it?

1045
01:14:17,064 --> 01:14:19,931
Or is it because you're a repressed,
hypocritical provincial...

1046
01:14:20,067 --> 01:14:23,559
...who didn't want to be seen
around town with a woman like me.

1047
01:14:24,071 --> 01:14:26,232
Yes, siree, you sure are enlightened.

1048
01:14:26,440 --> 01:14:30,672
I'm terribly sorry, I've made a mistake.
I thought you were one of the good guys.

1049
01:14:30,745 --> 01:14:32,940
Thank you for your time.

